args: *pant* Okay, where's the medicine?\nAnd are the fiends still here?\n...Oh!
There you are! I'm sorry, but the\ntownspeople need that more than you,\nso hand it over.
More of you? But I can't give up!\nTake this!
Is that the end of them...?
Ah! I think I'm in trouble here...
You've done really well, Sophie,\nbut let's handle the rest together.
Yeah, I'm fine. Just tell me what to do!
*pant* I think that...was the last of them...
Yeah, I don't see no more here.\nNice job with the fightin', folks!
Wait! We defeated the fiends, which is\nawesome, but what about the medicine?
It should be right... Oh no!
They've been gnawing on it pretty bad.\nMost of it is gone.
I wasn't able to retrieve the medicine.
And even if the medicine was destroyed,\nyou still protected the merchant's wagon!
For now, let's just scrounge up what we\ncan and haul it back to the Halidom, yeah?
...This is all we were able to recover.\nI'm so sorry we couldn't do more.
I appreciate your fine efforts, young lady.\nLuck was clearly just not with us today.
That said, those sick people in the village\nstill dearly need their medicine...
What do you think, Mom? I suppose we'll\nhave to head to another village and try\nto buy more, right?
I've a better idea. Thanks to this young\nlady's efforts, we can MAKE more.
Heh heh heh! We meet again,\nmy kind and brave hero.
You're the woman with the bad back!
Hang on. You know this lady, Mom?\nAlso, what was that bit you said earlier\nabout ＂making medicine＂?
I've been looking over the wagon you so\nhelpfully recovered, and it's coated from\nyoke to brake block with fiend scales!
These scales are very hard to come by,\nand you can use them to brew medicine\nthat works on all manner of ailments.

Indeed you did—although your friends
here also played no small part in it.
Please allow me to thank you again
properly in a few days.
For now, we need to get to the village\nand distribute the medicine. Thanks again!
Well done, Sophie. You defeated the\nfiends AND brought back their scales.
Yes, but I only managed the second part\nthrough pure coincidence.
Are ya kiddin' me? There were hardly any\ndamn fiends left by the time we got there!
If not for you running ahead, they would\nhave fled the area before we arrived.
Your desire to help people—your thoughts\nand actions—led directly to this result.
Yep! And that's what matters more\nthan success or failure.
Indeed, how you think and act matters\nfar more than the eventual outcome.
You've managed to touch a lot of people\naround here, Sophie.
If you keep it up, I know you'll be\na great companion dealie!
Oh. I feel so warm inside...
Yeah! And I also feel like that\nmurky feeling in my chest is gone too.
I think I understand a little better how to\nbe humanity's companion now.
And it's all thanks to my friends,\nboth new and old!
Actually, ya been pretty damn\ndepressed for days now.
Well, regardless, this is no time for rest.\nHave any new requests come in that I\nmight help with, {player_name}?
Well then, I'll just have to wait.\nBecause I'm humanity's companion...
And I will never stop trying!
